				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What tepples said, in terms of painting: Paint the large areas quickly with a wide roller, and paint the intricate areas with a small, precise brush. There's no reason to limit yourself to one or the other, which would result in a quick but sloppy or a precise but slow job. How do you know when you can use the wide roller? Hindsight is always 20/20, so don't paint until absolutely necessary, at which point you can look back and determine which brush is best.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

